2025/12/15 01:53:56 INFO dspy.teleprompt.gepa.gepa: Iteration 2: Proposed new text for generate_answer.predict: # Task Instruction: Iris Species Prediction
## Task Description
Predict the species of an iris plant based on its petal and sepal dimensions.

## Input Format
The input should be a dictionary with the following keys:
- `petal_length`: the length of the petal in cm
- `petal_width`: the width of the petal in cm
- `sepal_length`: the length of the sepal in cm
- `sepal_width`: the width of the sepal in cm

## Reasoning
The prediction is based on the dimensions of the sepal and petal, as the sepal dimensions are more indicative of the overall species classification in the iris dataset. However, a combination of both sepal and petal measurements should be considered to ensure accurate classification.

## Classification Rules
- Virginica (virginica) species:
  - Sepal length > 5.1 cm
  - Sepal width > 3.5 cm
  - Petal length > 1.5 cm
  - Petal width > 0.2 cm
- Versicolor (versicolor) species:
  - Sepal length > 5.5 cm
  - Sepal width < 3.2 cm
  - Petal length < 1.4 cm
- Setosa (setosa) species:
  - Sepal length < 5.1 cm
  - Sepal width < 3.5 cm
  - Petal length < 1.3 cm

## Feedback
The performance of the prediction model will be evaluated based on the following metrics:
- Accuracy: correct classification of the iris species
- Precision: proportion of correct predictions among all predictions
- Recall: proportion of correctly classified instances among all actual instances
- F1-score: harmonic mean of precision and recall

## Scoring
The task will be scored as follows:
- Correct classification: 1 point
- Incorrect classification: 0 points
- No input provided: 0 points

## Evaluation Criteria
The assistant's performance will be evaluated based on the accuracy and F1-score of the predictions. A higher score indicates better performance.

## Additional Information
The Iris dataset is a multiclass classification problem, and the classification rules above are based on the commonly used classification rules for the Iris dataset. The assistant should consider the intersection of the sepal and petal dimensions to make an accurate prediction.
