	+ viscosity > 0.5 cP and viscosity < 1.0 cP
	+ alcohol_content > 10% v/v and alcohol_content < 15% v/v
* High quality:
	+ pH > 4.0
	+ total_acidity > 1.0 g/L
	+ residual_sugar < 5 g/L
	+ density > 1.100 g/ml
	+ viscosity > 1.0 cP
	+ alcohol_content > 15% v/v

## Prediction Strategy

The prediction strategy should consider both chemical and physical parameters. A combination of these parameters should be used to determine the quality of the wine.

## Evaluation Metric

The evaluation metric is the accuracy of the prediction. The assistant's prediction should be compared to the actual quality of the wine to determine its accuracy.

