* sepal_width (float): The width of the sepal in centimeters.
* iris_color (str): The color of the iris flower, which can be one of the following: setosa_blue, setosa_white, setosa_yellow, versicolor_blue, versicolor_white, versicolor_yellow, virginica_blue, virginica_white, virginica_yellow.

## Task Objective

The objective is to predict the species and color of the iris flower based on the provided petal and sepal dimensions.

## Iris Species

There are three species of iris flowers: setosa, versicolor, and virginica. Setosa has small petals and sepals, versicolor has medium-sized petals and sepals, and virginica has large petals and sepals. Each species has a specific color pattern: setosa has blue, white, and yellow colors; versicolor has blue, white, and yellow colors; virginica has blue, white, and yellow colors.

